Johnny Edward Nigerian Aruna Quadri has been shortlisted to represent Africa at the Liebherr 2020 International Table Tennis Federation World Cup in China, The PUNCH reports. The event, scheduled to hold from November 13th to 15th, is expected to usher in the restart of ITTF competitions after several months of inactivity due to COVID-19. Quadri has been listed alongside African Cup champion Egypt’s Ahmed Saleh with the pair competing in the men’s event while African Cup women’s champion Dina Meshref of Egypt is the sole African representative in the women’s World Cup. Quadri was selected based on the world ranking.He is Africa’s highest-ranked player in the world at No. 20. He will be competing in his third consecutive World Cup and he is the first African to reach the quarter-finals of the competition, following his exploits at the 2014 edition in Dusseldorf, Germany. The men’s star-studded field includes China’s Ma Long, who is considered by many as the greatest table tennis player of all time. Long is joined by world No.1, Fan Zhendong (China), who lifted the 2019 Men’s World Cup in Chengdu, as well as a number of other top Asian players. Copyright PUNCH.
